and do nothing about that, can you?

783
01:17:04,120 --> 01:17:08,272
- It has absolutely nothing to do with you!
- It has everything to do with me.

784
01:17:08,320 --> 01:17:12,154
It's the least a mother
can do for her daugh...

785
01:17:12,200 --> 01:17:14,794
her daughter.

786
01:17:17,040 --> 01:17:20,999
That's something else
we need to have a chat about.

787
01:17:29,520 --> 01:17:33,399
They'd send me photos, now and again,
the nuns.

788
01:17:34,320 --> 01:17:37,118
This is one of your mother
when she was your age.

789
01:17:37,160 --> 01:17:40,038
Mom, you looked gorgeous.

790
01:17:41,960 --> 01:17:45,953
Aren't we forgetting
the small matter of dead bodies?

791
01:17:46,000 --> 01:17:49,595
How did you know about the other bodies?

792
01:17:51,160 --> 01:17:54,994
- What other bodies?
- You didn't know about the others.

793
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:57,634
What other bodies?

794
01:17:58,280 --> 01:18:00,874
Just Mr Brown's dog.

795
01:18:01,920 --> 01:18:04,514
And Mr Brown.

796
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:09,080
You killed them, too.

797
01:18:09,120 --> 01:18:11,998
I did it for you, dear.

798
01:18:16,840 --> 01:18:19,434
My mother...

799
01:18:20,040 --> 01:18:23,919
I've waited so long for you
to call me that.

800
01:18:30,880 --> 01:18:33,838
So, what do we do now?

801
01:18:33,960 --> 01:18:37,953
And when I'm asked: "Why do Vicars
always answer a question...

802
01:18:38,000 --> 01:18:41,595
by posing another question?",
I always reply:

803
01:18:41,760 --> 01:18:43,751
"Well, why shouldn't we?"

804
01:18:44,600 --> 01:18:47,797
But what, in the end,
all this comes down to,

805
01:18:47,840 --> 01:18:52,755
is how we deal in life
with the problems that we have to face.

806
01:18:54,000 --> 01:18:57,788
Sometimes it's a question
of just taking action,

807
01:18:57,840 --> 01:18:59,990
of making decisions,

808
01:19:00,040 --> 01:19:03,635
of involving others,
of finding your resolve,

809
01:19:03,680 --> 01:19:06,558
and seeing it through.

810
01:19:07,000 --> 01:19:11,790
But at other times,
it's about something much less tangible.

811
01:19:13,480 --> 01:19:18,190
Sometimes all it takes is a little grace.

812
01:19:35,320 --> 01:19:38,198
A little of God's grace,

813
01:19:40,280 --> 01:19:44,432
and all our problems seem to fade away.

814
01:19:52,400 --> 01:19:56,757
Now, should we demand
an explanation from our Lord?

815
01:19:58,240 --> 01:20:01,118
Question his methods?

816
01:20:01,240 --> 01:20:05,074
Or should we merely enjoy the benefits?

817
01:20:07,280 --> 01:20:08,872
Well,

818
01:20:09,600 --> 01:20:14,230
I don't think the good Lord
wants us to question too much.

819
01:20:15,720 --> 01:20:18,598
Isaiah, Chapter 55, verse 8:

820
01:20:19,600 --> 01:20:22,478
"My ways are not your ways."

821
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:27,999
And I think,
what he basically means by that is:

822
01:20:28,800 --> 01:20:31,678
"I'm mysterious, folks.

823
01:20:32,840 --> 01:20:35,434
Live with it."

824
01:20:40,960 --> 01:20:43,952
Thank you very much. Thank you.

825
01:20:53,080 --> 01:20:56,072
- Jesus Christ, I can't do it.
- It's alright.

826
01:20:56,120 --> 01:21:01,148
I didn't chop him up or anything
grizzly like that. Where are you going?

827
01:21:01,200 --> 01:21:04,158
- I'm not doing it.
- But I can't drive.

828
01:21:04,200 --> 01:21:07,397
- I'm not getting in the car.
- But, I'm a learner.

829
01:21:07,440 --> 01:21:11,558
- Officially I need someone with me.
- I think, under the circumstances...

830
01:21:11,600 --> 01:21:15,195
the normal rules do not apply.
Grace, wait.

831
01:21:19,080 --> 01:21:21,958
- Who is it?
- Mrs Parker.

832
01:21:27,520 --> 01:21:30,512
I suppose I have to use the pond again.

833
01:21:30,680 --> 01:21:32,477
Again?

834
01:21:32,880 --> 01:21:38,557
No, I don't want to know. I go inside,
and you do whatever you have to do.

835
01:21:39,200 --> 01:21:42,795
And I thought being an orphan
was a bad thing.

836
01:21:53,640 --> 01:21:56,518
My God, he's really stiff.

837
01:21:57,200 --> 01:22:02,035
- Holly, do you have to?
- I never saw anything like this before.

838
01:22:02,080 --> 01:22:03,877
My God.

839
01:22:03,960 --> 01:22:05,757
My God.

840
01:22:06,960 --> 01:22:09,838
My God, that's...

841
01:22:10,320 --> 01:22:12,914
It's just not fair.

842
01:22:13,840 --> 01:22:16,832
Other daughters get to plan weddings,

843
01:22:17,040 --> 01:22:20,555
and bake cakes, and go shopping
with their mothers. And what do I do?

844
01:22:20,600 --> 01:22:24,593
- Dispose of dead bodies.
- I could say the same, you know.

845
01:22:27,520 --> 01:22:30,398
Shall put the kettle on?

846
01:22:31,720 --> 01:22:35,998
Men were the downfall of the Jones women
for as long as there were Jones women,

847
01:22:36,040 --> 01:22:39,794
and that's why you have to be careful
about the types you bring home, dear.

848
01:22:39,840 --> 01:22:44,391
Wild and dangerous might be appealing now,
but believe me, you're on the same road.

849
01:22:45,200 --> 01:22:48,954
- You are.
- I should get me a boyfriend like Dad?

850
01:22:49,000 --> 01:22:54,632
- My God, you would, wouldn't you?
- There's nothing wrong with your father.

851
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:58,719
I knew you were a bitch to him,
but I always thought you loved him.

852
01:22:58,760 --> 01:23:01,354
I do love him.

853
01:23:01,440 --> 01:23:05,035
- I do love him.
- Then what about the letch?

854
01:23:05,360 --> 01:23:08,955
I'm assuming Dad doesn't know about him?

855
01:23:11,480 --> 01:23:16,679
Because I don't think he should,
I don't think he should know anything.

856
01:23:18,680 --> 01:23:21,672
- Right, Grace?
- Mom's the word, dear.

857
01:23:44,760 --> 01:23:48,230
-You're awake. I brought you some tea.
- Thank you.

858
01:23:48,280 --> 01:23:53,479
Mrs Parker, last night, do you think
she might have seen something?

859
01:23:55,640 --> 01:23:57,437
No, why?

860
01:23:58,400 --> 01:24:01,278
She's on her way over.

861
01:24:04,080 --> 01:24:07,436
- That doesn't mean to say she saw anything.
- Who?

862
01:24:07,480 --> 01:24:11,553
- What are you talking about?
- Mrs Parker, maybe she saw something.

863
01:24:11,600 --> 01:24:15,195
- She did not see anything last night.
- She saw you last night.

864
01:24:15,240 --> 01:24:17,196
- No.
- Possibly.

865
01:24:17,240 --> 01:24:20,755
- My God!
- I'll see to her.

866
01:24:20,800 --> 01:24:25,032
No, you won't. You'll stay right here.
You've seen to quite enough already.

867
01:24:25,080 --> 01:24:27,958
- My God.
- Just keep calm.

868
01:24:28,520 --> 01:24:31,512
Mrs. Goodfellow, did I wake you?

869
01:24:32,560 --> 01:24:36,553
- Actually, yes.
- I was hoping your husband would be home.

870
01:24:36,960 --> 01:24:40,157
- I need to speak to him.
- No, sorry, he's away.

871
01:24:40,200 --> 01:24:44,193
- He's on a three day convention.
- It's about the...

872
01:24:44,440 --> 01:24:47,432
the flower arranging committee.

873
01:24:51,040 --> 01:24:54,077
- you'll have to talk to him, not to me.
- Cynthia Martin...

874
01:24:54,120 --> 01:24:58,113
has been doing her level best
to undermine my leadership.

875
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:01,992
I believe she's planning a coup.

876
01:25:02,600 --> 01:25:05,478
- A coup?
- Behind my back, yes!

877
01:25:06,920 --> 01:25:09,912
If you don't mind, I just need to sit.

878
01:25:12,600 --> 01:25:16,593
Behind my back
and behind the Reverend's back as well.

879
01:25:17,360 --> 01:25:21,239
It's a disgrace.
I would even go as far as saying,

880
01:25:22,600 --> 01:25:26,195
it is amoral.
And knowing what I know now,

881
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:30,871
- I don't see how I can keep quiet.
- Jesus Christ, I knew it. She knows!

882
01:25:30,920 --> 01:25:36,199
