after all we've been through.

894
01:26:20,120 --> 01:26:24,830
- She knows! She was going to tell dad.
- About the flower arranging committee!

895
01:26:24,880 --> 01:26:28,475
This has nothing to do
with anything else...

896
01:26:29,600 --> 01:26:32,478
- Mrs Parker?
- Oh, dear.

897
01:26:33,480 --> 01:26:37,075
- Mrs Parker, can you hear me?
- Shit, is she...

898
01:26:39,080 --> 01:26:41,753
Yes, I believe she is.

899
01:26:41,800 --> 01:26:44,394
God. God.

900
01:26:45,880 --> 01:26:50,032
- She said herself, she had a dickey heart.
- I think you might have a dickey heart,

901
01:26:50,080 --> 01:26:54,232
- if someone came at you with a frying pan.
- Well, it was a simple misunderstanding,

902
01:26:54,280 --> 01:26:57,909
- it could happen to anybody.
- This cannot go on, mother! It is enough.

903
01:26:57,960 --> 01:27:01,953
- I understand you're upset, dear.
- I am! I've got two dead bodies.

904
01:27:02,000 --> 01:27:05,959
- One in the pond, one in the sitting room.
- You've got 3 dead bodies in the pond,

905
01:27:06,000 --> 01:27:08,992
- you forgot...
- I do not want to know.

906
01:27:09,040 --> 01:27:12,032
This has gone too far, and I mean it.

907
01:27:12,400 --> 01:27:14,994
I understand.

908
01:27:16,320 --> 01:27:19,915
I It's not
as if anyone's going to miss her.

909
01:27:21,840 --> 01:27:24,434
Mom? Dad is back.

910
01:27:25,480 --> 01:27:27,277
Hello!

911
01:27:30,120 --> 01:27:31,917
Hello!

912
01:27:34,560 --> 01:27:37,279
- There we are.
- Hello, sweetheart.

913
01:27:37,320 --> 01:27:40,551
- Hi, Dad.
- I'll tell you, I've just had the best...

914
01:27:40,600 --> 01:27:44,479
Sorry, I was saying,
I had the best convention.

915
01:27:46,040 --> 01:27:48,965
Hello, everyone. Mrs Parker.
How are you this morning?

916
01:27:49,050 --> 01:27:50,079
She's fine.

917
01:27:50,120 --> 01:27:54,079
- Darling, I thought it was three days.
- It was going to be three days, but...

918
01:27:54,120 --> 01:27:58,272
- It's so lovely to see you. - Bye, Dad.
I want to hear all about it.

919
01:27:58,320 --> 01:28:01,198
Well, I delivered my sermon.

920
01:28:02,560 --> 01:28:06,189
- And, how did it go?
- Very well, I even had them laughing.

921
01:28:06,240 --> 01:28:10,518
But you know what was really amazing?
It was what happened afterwards.

922
01:28:10,560 --> 01:28:14,553
Because I was getting praise
from everybody, from the counsel...

923
01:28:14,600 --> 01:28:18,991
and my peers. Normally that would be...
But you know what I was thinking?

924
01:28:19,040 --> 01:28:21,634
Why am I here?

925
01:28:22,680 --> 01:28:28,471
- Well, you've always been a deep thinker.
- When... what matters most to me...

926
01:28:28,520 --> 01:28:31,114
is back home.

927
01:28:33,880 --> 01:28:36,474
Oh, darling.

928
01:28:39,520 --> 01:28:41,112
So,

929
01:28:41,800 --> 01:28:46,999
they made love in every room in the house,
did they, Lilian and Brian?

930
01:28:47,400 --> 01:28:50,392
- And they went around twice.
- Twice.

931
01:28:50,920 --> 01:28:56,517
- I think we have some catching up to do.
- No, I have to see to Mrs Parker.

932
01:28:56,560 --> 01:29:01,270
- Yes. Do you need me?
- No, it's the flower arranging committee.

933
01:29:01,320 --> 01:29:04,039
I swear, it'll be the death of her.

