Mrs Parker would have approved.

938
01:29:26,040 --> 01:29:29,032
- Excellent sermon, Reverend.
- Thank you.

939
01:29:30,080 --> 01:29:33,117
- Thank you, goodbye.
- It was. It was very good.

940
01:29:33,160 --> 01:29:35,469
- Reverend Goodfellow.
- Mrs Martin.

941
01:29:35,520 --> 01:29:39,798
I wonder if we might have a talk about
the flower arranging committee this week.

942
01:29:39,840 --> 01:29:43,435
No, but perhaps next week.
I'll let you know.

943
01:29:44,306 --> 01:29:46,354
Very well.

944
01:29:49,480 --> 01:29:50,959
Goodbye.

945
01:30:35,760 --> 01:30:38,274
Who is it?

946
01:30:38,320 --> 01:30:41,198
- It's me.
- Come in.

947
01:30:55,120 --> 01:30:58,715
I think this is for the best, don't you?

948
01:31:10,680 --> 01:31:12,830
"My dearest Gloria,

949
